<paragraph id="8BC8A7412259FFB5FF0A2DC4FBD0633F" blockId="10.[136,1452,158,617]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="B9037B532259FFB5FF0A2DC4FEE860AA" bold="true" box="[189,265,482,508]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C77DCC22259FFB5FE912DC5FDCA60AA" authorityName="A. Jussieu" authorityYear="1833" box="[294,555,482,508]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malpighiaceae" genus="Byrsonima" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ligustrifolia">
<emphasis id="B9037B532259FFB5FE912DC5FDCA60AA" box="[294,555,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Byrsonima ligustrifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to 
<collectingCountry id="F360E7D12259FFB5FD662DC4FCF960AA" box="[721,792,482,508]" name="Brazil" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, it is distributed from the state of 
<collectingRegion id="49B369A32259FFB5FB2F2DC4FB3860AA" box="[1176,1241,482,508]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Bahia</collectingRegion>
to southern 
<collectingCountry id="F360E7D12259FFB5FAD02DC4FA4A60AA" box="[1383,1451,482,508]" name="Brazil" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Brazil</collectingCountry>
within the Atlantic Forest domain (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE6DAB02259FFB5FDA22E20FD2D6376" author="Francener, A." box="[533,716,518,544]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refId="ref17253" refString="Francener, A. (2020) Byrsonima in Flora do Brasil 2020. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / reflora / floradobrasil / FB 8827 (accessed 13 November 2020)" type="url" year="2020">Francener 2020</bibRefCitation>
). Its main features are the lanceolate leaves with acuminate apex and flowers with laterals petals white to pink and posterior petal white to pink becoming red in age with the claw yellow (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE6DAB02259FFB5FF542E68FE8F633E" author="Rolim, S. I. E." box="[227,366,590,616]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refId="ref18023" refString="Rolim, S. I. E. (2004) Revisao e redefinicao de Byrsonima Rich. ex Kunth subg. Macrozeugma Nied. (Malpighiaceae). Tese de doutorado. Universidade de Sao Paulo, 372 pp." type="book" year="2004">Rolim 2004</bibRefCitation>
), ovary glabrous and anthers and inflorescence axis tomentose.
</paragraph>
